All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    AlarmWrapper
    The alarm wrapper stores a list of alarms of type double associated with a symbol
    BollingerBands
    The class class BollingerBands defines the indicator “Bollinger Bands”.
    Candle
    Candle class, stores all relevant candle information.
    ChartController
    The Chart Controller class is responsible for receiving, generating and processing chart view events and, if necessary, manipulating data in the model.
    ChartRenderer
    The ChartRenderer class inherits from ChartRendererBase, is responsible for the actual drawing and implements the predefined render passes.
    ChartRendererBase
    The abstract class ChartRendererBase defines the basic variables, helpers and initialization methods as well as the signatures of the various render passes.
    ChartRendererVisualProfile
    Visual profile for the ChartPainter class.
    ChartType
    The chart type determines how the chart will be shown or rendered.
    ChartView
    The chart view is responsible for the graphic display of the stock chart information.
    ControllerBase
    This class forms the foundation of the two classes ControllerBaseDesktop and ControllerBaseInternal.
    ControllerBaseDesktop
    This class sets up the base for the DesktopController class.
    ControllerBaseInternal
    This class sets up the base for the gui controllers WatchlistController, SearchController, ChartController and PropertiesController.
    DatabaseActionListener
    Database action listener, used to ask the listener (i.e. the NetworkClient) for data input or subscription
    DatabaseController
    The database controller acts as an intermediary between the model of the data provider and the database model.
    DatabaseModel
    The database model is responsible for holding and processing the stock related data.
    DatabaseObserverPattern
    Observer pattern for the database (with 3 listener types DatabaseStockListener, DatabaseActionListener and DatabaseStatusListener)
    DatabaseStatusListener
    Database status listener, used to notify the listener (i.e. the NetworkClient) for data input or subscription
    DatabaseStockListener
    Database stock listener, used to notify the listener (i.e. the CharView) when StockData was added or updated.
    DataProviderProfile
    Stores the data used to connect to a data provider
    DataProviderProfileTableModel
    Table model to render and handle the available DataProviderProfile objects
    DesktopController
    The desktop controller class is responsible for constructing the GUI controller classes and executing certain calls of the ControllerBaseDesktop class
    DesktopView
    Defines the desktop view
    DesktopViewBase
    Basic layout class for the desktop frame.
    DialogAlarm
    The alarm dialog gives the user the option to add or remove new alarms.
    DialogAlarmTriggered
    Defines the alarm triggered dialog.
    DialogDataProviderProfil
    Dialog to set a new DataProviderProfil object
    DialogIndicator
    The indicator dialog gives the user the option to add or remove new indicators.
    DialogIndicatorParameter
    The indicator parameter dialog, to get user input for the indicator dialog.
    DialogViewBase
    Base class for all dialog frames
    DisplayType
    The display type determines "where" the data will be shown or rendered.
    FrameProfile
    The frame profiles are used to contain data about all the different gui frames i.e. size, position.
    FrameProfileBase
    This defines the base of the frame profiles
    FrameProfileChart
    The chart frame profiles are used to contain data about gui frames and additional chart frame data i.e. symbol and indicators.
    IndicatorBase
    This abstract class is a basis of the indicators.
    IndicatorType
    Enum to name and identify an indicator
    InternalViewBase
    Basic layout class for the (internal) child frames.
    MenuBarChart
    Menu bar of the chart view
    MenuBarDesktop
    Defines the desktop menu bar
    NetworkClient
    The abstract class NetworkClient is an extension of the class DatabaseController and organizes the connection to a server as well as the sending and receiving of various requests.
    PersistenceDataWrapper
    The PersistenceDataWrapper class is responsible for persisting and restoring the relevant model data.
    PriceWrapper
    The PriceWrapper class contains 3 pieces of information, a double for the price, a double for the price difference (compared to the previous price), and a boolean flag for the status of the timer.
    PropertiesController
    The Properties Controller class is responsible for receiving, generating and processing properties view events and, if necessary, manipulating data in the model.
    PropertiesFrameListener
    Listens to changes in regards to frame profiles or indicators.
    PropertiesListener
    Listens to changes in the properties model.
    PropertiesModel
    The properties model contains administrative data (user data or server connection data) as well as data relating to window-frames, indicators and GUI standard settings.
    PropertiesObserverPattern
    Observer pattern for the properties model (with 2 listener types PropertiesFrameListener and PropertiesListener)
    PropertiesTabPanelBase
    Base class for the properties tab panels.
    PropertiesTabPanelChart
    The chart tab enables the user to change certain settings regarding the chart view
    PropertiesTabPanelData
    The data tab enables the user to create, select or remove new data provider profiles.
    PropertiesTabPanelGeneral
    The General Tab allows the user to change certain settings regarding frame size and the like.
    PropertiesView
    The Properties view shows the general "settings" regarding the application as well as server connection settings.
    PullClient
    Pull client for http requests
    PullData
    PullData class, temporarily contains the historic data, when received from provider.
    PullQuoteData
    PullQuoteData class, temporarily contains the historic data, when received from provider.
    PullSearchData
    PullSearchData class, temporarily contains the search data, when received from provider.
    PushClient
    Websocket "push" client, handles the subscription requests for the real-time data.
    PushData
    PushData class, temporarily contains the real-time data, when received from provider.
    PushRequest
    PushRequest class, used to subscribe/unsubscribe symbols, and is send to provider.
    SearchController
    The Search Controller class is responsible for receiving, generating and processing search view events and, if necessary, manipulating data in the model.
    SearchView
    Representation of information of the Search to the user.
    Serializer
    The helper class Serializer is a collection of converter methods to convert JSON data into objects and vice versa.
    SerializerAdapter<T>
    Helps to serialize subtyped classes as frame profiles or indicators
    SimpleMovingAverage
    The SimpleMovingAverage class defines the “Simple Moving Average” indicator.
    StockData
    This class contains various data about a particular stock.
    StockDataCalculator
    The function of this class is, above all, the calculation, processing or preparation of real-time StockDataRealtime and historical data StockDataHistoric.
    StockDataHistoric
    StockDataHistoric class, stores all relevant historic data, received from a data provider.
    StockDataQuote
    StockDataQuote class, stores all relevant quote data, received from a data provider.
    StockDataRealtime
    StockDataRealtime class, stores all relevant quote data, received from a data provider.
    StockDataSearch
    StockDataSearch class, stores all relevant search data, received from a data provider.
    StockDataState
    This class implements mainly an Enum StockDataStateType, that regulates the various availability states access, no_access and unclear of the (pull) data.
    StockDataState.StockDataStateType
    Describes the state of accessibility of stock data
    Stocker_3285766_Kaplan_Christoph
    Stocker ProPra entry class
    StockerApplicationManager
    Stocker application manager, is primarily responsible for starting, constructing and terminating the application.
    StockerCheckBoxRenderer  
    StockerColorField
    Defines a label with the function to choose a color.
    StockerDefaultRenderer
    Table renderer used for watchlist view table
    StockerTable
    The class StockerTable is used in the watchlist and search view and is derived from JTable.
    StockerTableModel
    The table model implements a list of the StockData type and overrides the common AbstractTableModel methods in such a way that the list can be accessed and displayed correctly.
    StockerTextField
    text field class that extends JTextField and adds a document filter to check user input
    StockerTextField.FilterMethod
    Interface that implements the filter method to check if user input is valid.
    TimeInterval
    The time interval determines the resolution and the time window of the considered stock data
    ViewBase
    interface for all "MVC-View" frames/windows.
    ViewType
    The frame type determines the type of view
    WatchlistController
    The Watchlist Controller class is responsible for receiving, generating and processing watchlist view events and, if necessary, manipulating data in the model.
    WatchlistMenuBar
    Defines the watchlist menu bar.
    WatchlistView
    Representation of information of the Watchlist to the user.
